INRAE does not describe the concept, and its context (as defined under 'egrigultural machinery and equipment') seems more specific then near-matching concepts from other vocabularies. If we were to assume a broad definition, there are some exact matches: NCIT https://ontobee.org/ontology/NCIT?iri=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C133237, Wikidata https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q5375483, 
Ecotoxicology https://loterre.istex.fr/3WV/fr/page/-B6V0SD2Q-2?clang=en
The concepts have exact matches, but parent / child clasifications contain some differences. (most notably for NALT)

There is a very specific difference between elemental and atomic oxigen (the former is described by EnvThes and is what exact matches were found for). Uberon and CIDO use the imported term from CHeBI; https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/uberon/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FCHEBI_25806, https://ontobee.org/ontology/CIDO?iri=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_25806

There is a very specific difference between elemental and atomic carbon (the later was referred to by CHeBI and is what exact matches were found for). UBERON and CIDO use the imported term from CHeBI: https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/uberon/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FCHEBI_27594, https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/cido/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FCHEBI_27594
CIDO uses the imported term from UBERON: https://ontobee.org/ontology/CIDO?iri=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000178
CIDO does use an Imported term for Patient from OMRSE: https://ontobee.org/ontology/CIDO?iri=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OMRSE_00000030
Link in NPO seems to be broken, exact matches were found for https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/NPO/?p=classes&lang=en&conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fpurl.bioontology.org%2Fontology%2Fnpo%23NPO_199
gold(0) is a very specific entity in ChEBI, there are several vocabularies that include terms that are exact matches for its parent classes 'elemental gold' and 'gold molecular entity'
